name: Attack on Titan: Before the Fall
description: missed out for this to be bl between kuklo and xavi but what do i know. either way the story was very bipolar and all over the place. it needed like 10 extra chapters at least to setup stakes, i get why kuklo and sharle care about each other, they talked for like two years but i didnt have enough time to care about either of them. on top of that, why the fuck this guy thinks hes a titans son because i still dont know. like i know they told him that he is but hes very clearly not. sharle has no purpose other than providing stakes which kind of sucks when she should have been way more important to the story. i also didnt like how cringy the dialogue was at points, like i appreciate that its a shounen manga but still this is bad even for a shounen and a lot of sections of the manga were retreading ground from the original just like worse. the art redeems is the main redeeming factor because its straight fire.

name: Blue Heaven
description: despite feeling a bit dated the artwork is very nice. i was pretty engaged with this one for the first few chapters but at a point it just kind of devolved into random bullshit going on and it was just a bit all over the place to build any semblance of tension.

name: Voices of a Distant Star
description: the kind of thing you forget the moment you finish it. 0 impact on anything, it wasnt a bad time though, just a nothing time. i mean that might be account of it being like 10 chapters long but it really just doesnt have enough time to do anything it wants to. like if you only have two volumes dont pick both romance and mecha.

name: Wonder Cat Kyuu-chan
description: it does its job of being cute and silly and you can finish it in less than an hour

name: Kubera
description: imagine tower of god if the art was even more shit and the story was even more boring

name: MAD
description: i have no idea why this is bordering on a 7 on mal, this is a very promising first eight chapters and i think ill keep up with this series. maybe its just because im a fiend for post apocolyptic stories though.

name: Grandmaster of Demonic Cultivation - Mo Dao Zu Shi
description: the homosexual chinese are the only people who can make good manhua. too bad a bit too much is left unexplained, and no im not watching the drama to figure it out. im also not a massive fan of how the art develops but thats neither here nor there as ive seen a bunch of people who do like it.

name: Sasaki and Miyano
description: boy loveception. i didnt find the story that special or interesting, its above average but surely not worthy of #1 bl manga on mal

name: Azumanga Daioh
description: when the best character is a pedophile thats when you know youve fucked up

name: East of West
description: im sorry but this shit is so overrated, it could not keep me engaged at all and while some panels look good often the art style just kind of looks like shit to me at least. the world building was above average though.

name: The Slumbering Ranker
description: not even good enough to be slop, he wakes up chapter one op. like where are you meant to go from there? also its a vr mmorpg manhwa and those just suck ass by default

name: Our Aimless Nights
description: very middle of the road romance manga, doesnt do anything bad but its not doing anything particularly well. saving grace is probably it being 25 chapters because if this was like 60 i wouldnt have been able to finish it.

name: Purple Hyacinth
description: kym is such a stupid ass name i cannot take it and at the start the exposition was so forced, they could have just had the dating helps you moving on line but ig they thought i was stupid.

name: My Girlfriend Is an Orc Warlord!
description: basically no story with gags that dont do anything for me

name: Something is Killing the Children
description: kind of corny sometimes but its a good time and i really like the art style. i dont like how it feels like events dont have the impact they should though.

name: Saga
description: this series was so fucking weird, tvs having sex, planet babies, people banging spiders, little seal guys who walk around, race wars and sextillion. ive changed the score like 4 times from 7 to 6 to 8 to now 8.5. idk maybe ill make it a 1 in a week who knows.

name: Unsounded
description: the main character is so fucking annoying and it just wasnt that interesting. only a 5 because the art went hard every once in a while for some reason even though most of a time it was mid.

name: Childhood Friend of the Zenith
description: lots of praise for this on r/manhwa because they have brain damage. its standard murim slop that will 100% have a future harem.

name: In the Room
description: carried by the monster designs. that shit was fire.

name: High School Musical
description: read this because it was lowest on mal. its real bad but i reckon its only a 2 bc its based on high school musical. change the names and its gonna be sitting at a 6.4 on mal.

name: Build King
description: 0 potential thank god they pulled the plug on it

name: The Baengri Clan's Unwanted Granddaughter
description: its a fine murim (kind of??) manga. im not 100% sure what genre trying to be but its an alright time waster.

name: Omori
description: i dont know why they are making an omori manga, it just seems like a bizarre choice to retell a game in manga form. i like the art a lot so far and the story is omori which i thought was only pretty alright. i also feel like it should have been english originally and then go to japanese?? like omori was most popular in america, maybe to spread its influence but in that case i would have made it in chinese or something. who knows.

name: Tokyo-hatsu Isekai-yuki
description: a pretty alright set of 9 short stories, not a massive fan of the dating looking art though

name: Wistoria: Wand and Sword
description: the art is sometimes incredible, the story on the other hand had me constantly cringing. if they got an actual good author on this it could have been so great. id still read if you like seeing pretty panels every few chapters.

name: Don't Destroy Humanity
description: could have become a 7 if it had more time to expand but it got cut off too soon :( i also wasnt a massive fan of the tl frying to guilt trip the readers saying its our fault it got cancelled and shit. mf you were the one giving it to use for free, how you trying to take the high road.

name: The Big Bees
description: they're just such silly little guys !!

name: Silver Spoon
description: i know a lot of people like this, i just dont. couldnt get invested idk. maybe ill come back at some point tho.

name: Kami no Kodomo
description: went for something mature and deep but just ended up a series of disturbing events and a main character who is the worst and just never gets redeemed, hes just the worst the whole time for some reason idk either.

name: I Like You Who Can Have Sex Anyone.
description: its porn. i know i should have thought that from the title but it wasnt listed as porn so i thought maybe it was a real story about people with like a fucked up sex life or something?? (idk what i was thinking)

description: boichi is actually so shit at drawing girls its honestly insane. this feels closer to softcore porn then a oneshot. the fight is pretty good too but i just cannot read this with a straight face i just feel silly.

description: just going through my backlog of bad manga i dropped at this point. the gamer is shit straight from the start till (i assume) the end. the art is genuinely awful, often worse then tower of god but where tower of god succeeded in story, the gamer didnt and was just felt silly to read.

name: Seven Deadly Sins
description: i didnt make it through this one. if anyone wants to write a shounen id first read this adn then if you feel yourself writing something similar make drastic changes.

name: My Hero Academia
description: it finished recently (as of writing this) so i took that as a chance to finish it. the ending was just as unsatisfying as everyone said it was and a really bad way to end a pretty alright shounen manga. the art was easily its best aspect tho shit was fire.

name: Miss Kobayashi's Dragon Maid
description: when you make your characters children and still do fanservice :3

name: Mushoku Tensei: Jobless Reincarnation
description: ive been this series #1 opp for a little while now but didnt put it here bc i thought i already did lol. anyways this manga/anime is kind of like im the fated villain in the way that the mc is an irredeemable pos thats impossible to root for. i gave this +0.1 though because he hasnt raped anyone (i think). the manga is also worse pedophile wise (or better if you are a pedo) than the anime. i know this is really popular and my only thought for a reason why is that anime fans are all pedophiles anyways so they dont care.

name: The Hitman's Fave
description: mildly entertaining but repetitive manga. i can see this going a max of 20 chapters unless it finds some different jokes.

name: Bunny Drop
description: get rid of the incest at the end and we're getting somewhere. i liked the entire thing up till there and it just threw it out the window. <--- actually edit it was pretty bad even without the fucked ending. especially the ugly as shoujo art style.

name: Solo Leveling: Ragnarok
description: we're really early on rn but so far its art is very pretty like the original and the story is intriguing so far. hoping it will be as well executed as the original.

description: i genuinely could not not tell you who this is for. do middle aged japanese men read villainess manga?

name: Grashros

name: Ambivalent: Dotei wo Sutetara Shinu Sekai

name: Kuchibeta Shokudou
description: shoutout to moosyu for translating chapter 52. what a nice guy!!

name: I'm the Fated Villain
description: i get that the mc is a villain and thats the whole idea but also how does the author expect me want a mc to succeed after he rapes someone? like what the fuck. and it is treated with about the tact you'd expect of a manhua author, they tried to make it into a joke and from what i hear later on shes gonna fall in love with him?? does the author think that absolves him?? anyways if you have any disagreements with my take i suggest you kill yourself because the world would be better off without you anyways.

name: The Outcast Is Too Good at Martial Arts
description: the art in this one is real weird, my best guess is that its a 3d model using shaders to make it look like its 2d art? anyways the story is boring and the weird 2d 3d hybrid art looks like shit.

name: Juvenile Prison
description: the art is very good, the story is boring generic gang fighting manhwa. mc is mad so mc beats up big man, repeat until final boss.

name: My S-Class Hunters
description: the art is quite nice, the story and characters are quite shit

name: Reality Quest
description: reality quest: at its best its a slightly above average gang manhwa. it has a lot of issues but i'd rather talk about the least important one, why does the artist draw the girls in a pornhwa artstyle?? not to say i'm gay its just that i'm not attracted to the weird ass pornhwa proportions, like if you look for more then a second everything goes to shit, their cardboard personalities dont help either though that isnt specific to the girls, the guys are paper thin too. though this didn't seem like a problem for the average reader as from the comments most people who read this are 13.

name: Down To Earth
description: probably the last time ill read an english webtoon. i dont know how to say this but they all give off such an aura of being gay, its like the same vibe tumblr gives off. even the straight ones give it off. this isnt even to say im homophobic, ive straight up read manhwa closer to gay porn and its felt less gay then this. i truly cannot explain it. sadly this one doesnt have the quality nevermore does to offset that.

description: very generic ecchi romance thing even though it has more ecchi then romance. there was more then one boob grab in the first 10 chapters thats all im saying.

name: Kingdom
description: big fights between big chinese men, peak fiction. the story is entertaining and the stakes are always high because even though the mc cant die it feels like anyone can die at any moment. my only issue is theres a lot of pedo shit and i get like its ancient china its probably realistic but dude, nobody was wiping out dozens of soliders in a single sword swing i dont think you were aiming for too much realism here.

description: beautiful art with a pretty interesting mystery. felt a bit short but apparently there is another one called aisha which might solve my issues, ill check it out when it finishes. the incest definitely didnt help this manhuas situation though.

description: i just wasnt feeling this one, it was fine but i just wasnt that interested

description: sadly it seems japan as a country is incapable to be funny. there are less then 40 chapters so i guess they knew the gag would get old quick but i only read one volume so i guess they overestimated how much i want to waste my time.

description: at the start the setting has the vibe of an unintentional dystopian hellscape which im not 100% against with pacing that isnt borderline schizophrenic and has actual character development. a lot of apologising though.

name: My Dress-Up Darling
description: this is 50% fanservice 50% something else and im not even sure what the something else is but its not good at either. if i wanted porn id watch porn. this is definitely not a 9 as it somehow got on comick but the recent arc has unironically been really great (like an 8). unfortunately thats because it is so different from the rest of the manga (the latest arc being the one where she cosplays as kmart griffith).

description: can we stop giving people making boring romance manga money please

description: goblin slayer wants to be berserk so bad

description: got my heart pumping so much it probably decreased my life expectancy by like 3 years

name: Hunter x Hunter
description: its fun and has pretty dark themes considering it is a shonen. kind of repetitive in some arcs though.

name: Homunculus
description: wow this is pretty coo- AUUGGUIFAA AAAAHHHH IAISODADOJOJOGF BNBMVMFIADKADKDFLLGF AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA AHFHHHHHHHHajffhjf :( cool story but sometimes gets so disgusting i have to take a multiple day break from reading it

name: Blue Period
description: great story with interesting character development especially because his development is a lot more abstract then other stories, also how is the most hot girl actually and a man. my only issues are that at some stages it gets kind of boring and also later on it creates characters that seem unrealistic and kind of one dimensional (granted ive never been to art school) but for a world set in our world the characters just seem a little too eccentric.

name: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part 8: Jojolion
description: not on the same level as the previous part but jojolion still has intriguing story and an interesting mystery even if the villain isnt very good especially when you compare him to valentine. on a side note no matter how much ariki tries to pretend the jojos are straight they are clearly all raging homosexuals jousuke got a boner when he looked behind yasuho and saw joushu im telling you.

name: Grappler Baki
description: baki is not a good story in almost any way, not art, characters or story but it makes up for that with pure entertainment value. baki is some of the most insane, bizarre and entertaining shit that anyones ever made. my eyes stayed stuck to this shit stained page the entire time.

name: Helck
description: an entertaining twist on the average fantasy world

name: The Girl From the Other Side
description: great art style with a old fashioned picture book kind of vibe that makes every page interesting to look at. an interesting world and the curse is a cool idea. i liked all of the cast. my only issues with it is that it felt as if it ended a bit sooner then i would have liked. i think it needed more time to flesh out its ideas and so the ending would make more sense because reading the ending was really confusing (or i might just be stupid) but even with confusing buts once i fully understood it i think it was a decent conclusion.

name: Vinland Saga
description: the art is stunning the characters are interesting, especially askeladd and thorfinn who both are horrible people who have done horrible things but you cant help but enjoy their presences. thorkell is also really entertaining to watch and is basically a dorohedoro character. my only gripes with this series are that it feels so grounded in reality that when a silly manga moment or something outlandish happens it really takes me out of it and that the whole idea of having no enemies just seems too idealistic in such a realistic world.

name: Something About Us
description: i usually read shit romance to relax me and to burn time. i love to complain about romance manhwa and manga being shit but if they get too good i just dont read them. this did most things well but tragically i hated almost everyone and it was a bit miserable at times so it definitely didnt relax me. its a pretty good read if you like romance as a genre but if youre like me its kind of a slog to get through.

name: 20th Century Boys
description: great start and its really cool when you understand every part of it. the art and panelling are great and urasawa makes everything cinematic. i like almost all of the cast especially otcho and his journey. the story kind of drags but i was still interested the whole time. the ending was a massive fumble in my opinion even if you include 21st century boys as the same manga, prior to the ending i considered 20th century boys to be a high 9 maybe even a 10 but if you dont include 21st century boys i would say it becomes an 8. even including 21st century boys its still only a low 9 as i found the final reveal dissatisfying and i still had questions left.

name: Arakawa Under the Bridge
description: it was pretty funny sometimes but every chapter is like 8 pages with one joke per and there are more than 400. i breezed through the first 100 but it got really repetitive, similar issues that i felt with komi cant communicate.

name: A Business Proposal
description: its another predictable romance manhwa. the art is fine, the story is nothing special but its not that bad just not my cup of tea and the characters are fine as well but it entertained me enough to finish it also my brother saw me reading this and now i think he thinks of me as less of a man. its easy to skim as well and i think i got about the same experience with a quarter of the reading. i think her brother is also a closet homosexual because like he didnt know it was a girl, he was just into a guy.

name: One Piece
description: honestly the more one piece i read the more just fatigued i feel. i just cant love a series that has no stakes, nobody ever dies and i know death isnt the only way to build stakes but one piece is the kind of story where death should happen, its a bunch of pirates shooting at each other in a sea where if the mc falls in he dies and it feels like oda pulling it out his ass when somehow everyone survives. how am i meant to care about massive fights when i know the characters could just wait a week after then do it again. i still think one piece is a good manga but i dont think its as great as i first thought when i had only read 100 chapters.

name: The Climber
description: the start of the climber is bad, like 4/10 type writing completely carried by the art where there is zero subtlety with anything, like straight up the teacher says 'could it be something in his past that made him shut his heart'. it had bad pacing like they said that mori is changing after knowing him for like 2 weeks and it felt slow and fast at the same time somehow so i probably would have dropped this but apparently after volume 3 the original author left and the artist had to do his job for him, and the artist immediately killed off most of the side characters literally or by turning them into whores. he changed the plot from a sports manga to a psychological manga with climbing as a backdrop to it with a massive amount of symbolism and the art kept getting better and better and by the final climb it had reached a peak as high as even berserk and vagabond in my opinion. the final climb was probably my favourite arc and ending in all of manga and hit so hard not knowing if he would live or die until the very end. i did not move for the entire duration of it. this is peak literally and figuratively (im a comedic genius).

name: My Boss's Special Request
description: how did they fit bad characters with a loser mc who complains too much, a boring plot, bad comedy, found time to fit in a cliche why is my heart beating so fast scene and had him defend the boss from trash talk less than 10 chapters after he did the same thing all in a single package? the only saving grace from this dropping any lower is that the side plot about the celebrity guy getting 0 bitches was pretty funny and also you can read 40 chapters of it in like an hour.
